---
// This component demonstrates Vercel Image Optimization features
---

<div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8 space-y-8">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">How Vercel Image Optimization Works</h2>
  
  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">Without Optimization</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-muted-foreground">
        <li>• Original PNG: ~500KB</li>
        <li>• No responsive sizing</li>
        <li>• Single format for all browsers</li>
        <li>• Loads immediately (blocks render)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-green-600 dark:text-green-400">With Vercel Optimization</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-muted-foreground">
        <li>• WebP/AVIF: ~150KB (70% smaller!)</li>
        <li>• Multiple sizes generated</li>
        <li>• Modern format for modern browsers</li>
        <li>• Lazy loading below the fold</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-muted/50 rounded-lg p-6 space-y-4">
    <h3 class="font-semibold">What Happens Behind the Scenes:</h3>
    <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
      <li>You upload image.png to your project</li>
      <li>Astro's Image component requests it</li>
      <li>Vercel intercepts the request</li>
      <li>Optimizes on-the-fly: format, size, quality</li>
      <li>Caches result at edge locations</li>
      <li>Serves optimized version to users</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</div>